properties":{"toHash":"8326963f7fc9869c5fb55d77f79347a9d0d27893","current":true,"fromHash":"5b82a20736fb73dd7df8f6371a7d800a13a5036d"}}},{"id":13565,"createdDate":1773755405210,"user":{"name":"talr","emailAddress":"ofir.f@codium.ai","active":true,"displayName":"Qodo Bot","id":55,"slug":"talr","type":"NORMAL","links":{"self":[{"href":"https://bitbucket.dev.codium-inc.com/users/talr"}]}},"action":"COMMENTED","commentAction":"ADDED","comment":{"properties":{"repositoryId":142},"id":9123,"version":0,"text":"\uD83D\uDD34 **Action Required**\n\n1\\. Wrong word counting `\uD83D\uDC1E Bug` `✓ Correctness`\n\ncount_words() uses text.split(\" \"), which counts empty strings for repeated spaces and does not\ntreat other whitespace (tabs/newlines) as separators, producing incorrect word counts. This also\ndiverges from the repo’s existing tokenization/counting behavior in\npipeline.tokenize()/count_tokens().\n\n\n**Agent Prompt:**\n\n```\n### Issue description\n`count_words()` currently uses `text.split(\" \")`, which yields incorrect word counts for strings containing multiple spaces and does not treat other whitespace (tabs/newlines) as separators. This also conflicts with existing whitespace tokenization in `pipeline.tokenize()`.\n\n### Issue Context\nThe repository already tokenizes with `text.lower().split()` (no delimiter), and `count_tokens()` is built on top of that; `count_words()` should align to avoid contradictory counting.\n\n### Fix Focus Areas\n- string_utils.py[11-13]\n- pipeline.py[1-3]\n- pipeline.py[10-11]\n```\n\nⓘ _Copy this prompt and use it to remediate the issue with your preferred AI generation tools_","author":{"name":"talr","emailAddress":"ofir.f@codium.ai","active":true,"displayName":"Qodo Bot","id":55,"slug":"talr","type":"NORMAL","links":{"self":[{"href":"https://bitbucket.dev.codium-inc.com/users/talr"}]}},"createdDate":1773755405206,"updatedDate":1773755405206,"comments":[],"threadResolved":false,"severity":"NORMAL","state":"OPEN","permittedOpera